# Serve the install script at https://frugal.sh/install with a 200 rewrite so
# `curl -fsSL https://frugal.sh/install | sh` gets the script bytes directly,
# not a 302 redirect that would leak the raw.githubusercontent.com URL to the
# terminal on slow links.
#
# NOTE: These URLs point at the current repo location (brainsparker/frugal).
# If the repo is ever transferred to the frugalsh org (to match `install.sh`
# and README branding), update every row below. The install.sh bytes served
# here also need `REPO="..."` updated in tandem.
/install      https://raw.githubusercontent.com/brainsparker/frugal/main/install.sh   200
/install.sh   https://raw.githubusercontent.com/brainsparker/frugal/main/install.sh   200

# Convenience redirects so links from talks/blogs land on the canonical docs.
/github       https://github.com/brainsparker/frugal                                  301
/docs         https://github.com/brainsparker/frugal#readme                           301
/security     https://github.com/brainsparker/frugal/blob/main/SECURITY.md            301
/license      https://github.com/brainsparker/frugal/blob/main/LICENSE                301
